Reference : https://medium.com/@olayinkasamuel44/how-to-deploy-a-static-website-to-s3-bucket-using-github-actions-ci-script-fa1acc932fbd

Create a new repository
> Create a IAM User and setup creds with GitHub Action
> GitHub > Repo Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions
 > New Repository Secret > Add :

1.  AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
2.  AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY

> Create an AWS S3 Bucket
> Enable Static Website hosting in bucket and also enable ACL 


> GitHub > Repo Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions
 > New Repository Secret > Add :

3.

> Go to GitHub Repo > Actions > Setup a workflow for yourself

main.yaml

>
name: Upload Website

on:
  push:
    branches:
    - main

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
    - name: Checkout
      uses: actions/checkout@v1

    - name: Configure AWS Credentials
      uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v1
      with:
        aws-access-key-id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}
        aws-secret-access-key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}
        aws-region: us-east-1

    - name: Deploy static site to S3 bucket
      run: aws s3 sync . s3://BUCKET_NAME --delete


> Check > Actions in GitHub Repo
> GO to S3 bucket > index.html > Allow public read permissions
> Copy Object URL > Paste in another tab
 
